# =============================================
# AsymmFlow - .gitignore
# =============================================

# === Secrets & local runtime state (NEVER commit) ===
.auth_token.json
*.auth_token.json
.field_crypto_salt
backups/
*_BACKUP*.db
SYNTHETIC_IDENTITY.local.md

# === Build Artifacts ===
build/
*.exe
*.dll

# Ignore all build-output dist/ directories everywhere...
dist/
# ...but keep frontend/dist with a committed placeholder index.html so
# `go:embed all:frontend/dist` in main.go compiles on a fresh clone before the
# frontend has been built (`npm run build` / `wails build` regenerates the rest).
!frontend/dist/
frontend/dist/*
!frontend/dist/index.html
*.dylib
*.so
*.app

# === Dependencies ===
node_modules/
frontend/node_modules/

# === Environment & Secrets ===
.env
.env.local
.env.production
# .env.example is committed (template without secrets)

# Hardware-ID sidecars — key-derivation material, must NEVER be tracked
# (.hardware_id plaintext, .hardware_id.dpapi DPAPI-wrapped, .hardware_id.migrated backup)
.hardware_id
.hardware_id.*

# === Databases ===
*.db
*.db-wal
*.db-shm
*.db-journal
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3

# === IDE / Editor ===
.vscode/settings.json
.vscode/launch.json
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# === OS Files ===
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
Desktop.ini
ehthumbs.db

# === Logs ===
*.log
*.out
crash_log.*

# === Test Artifacts ===
coverage.out
test-results/
playwright-report/
*.test.exe

# === Vite Temp Files ===
*.timestamp-*.mjs

# === Generated Output ===
exports/intelligence/
batch_output/
test_output/

# === Archives & Packages ===
*.zip
*.7z
*.tar.gz
*.tar
*.rar
deploy_package/AsymmFlow_Deploy_*/
deploy_package/AsymmFlow.app/
deploy_package/AsymmFlow.exe
deploy_package/.env
deploy_package/ph_holdings.db
deploy_package/data/ph_holdings.db

# === Temporary Files ===
*.tmp
*.bak
*.backup
nul

# === Business Documents (NEVER commit) ===
Bank_Statements/
Costing_Sheets/
Offers*/

# === Mac Dev Setup (local only) ===
mac_dev_setup/

# === AI Tool Config (local only) ===
.agent/
.claude/
.gitnexus

# Keep durable project-level Codex instructions/config trackable, but ignore runtime state.
.codex/cache/
.codex/logs/
.codex/sessions/
.codex/tmp/

# Generated marketing PDFs (build artifacts of docs/marketing/generate_pdfs.py; regenerate from the scrubbed .md sources)
docs/marketing/*.pdf
